
've successfully created a comprehensive C4ISR (Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance) system with a microservices architecture and graphical interface. Here's what has been built:
🏗️ System Architecture
Microservices Backend:
Device Management Service - Manages military devices, telemetry, and real-time tracking
Intelligence Service - Handles intelligence reports and threat assessment
Communication Service - Manages inter-service communication and WebSocket connections
Air Support Service - Coordinates air support requests and mission tracking
Map Service - Provides geospatial data and mapping capabilities
User Management Service - Handles authentication and role-based access control
Frontend Dashboard:
React-based interface with real-time updates
Interactive map visualization using Leaflet
Real-time data streaming via WebSockets
Modern UI with Tailwind CSS
Infrastructure:
Kong API Gateway - Routes and secures all API calls
PostgreSQL - Primary database with PostGIS for geospatial data
Redis - Caching and real-time communication
Prometheus + Grafana - Monitoring and observability
Docker Compose - Complete containerization
